{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Hyperspectral imaging (HSI) is an advanced technology that combines a spectrometer and a camera sensor to capture detailed spatial and spectral data.",
    "This technique helps detect different chemical and physical properties in food and related products (He and Sun 2015; Wang et al. 2021a; Sun et al. 2024; Ahmed et al. 2024a).",
    "HSI captures and processes images that offer detailed information about the spectral properties of a scene or object.",
    "Unlike standard imaging techniques, HSI collects images over a much broader range of narrow spectral bands, often spanning from tens to hundreds of bands (Kamruzzaman 2023).",
    "This wide range of spectral bands enables the identification of specific information about the chemical composition, material properties, and other physical characteristics of food in an image (Elmasry et al. 2012)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "This technique helps detect different chemical and physical properties in food and related products (He and Sun 2015; Wang et al. 2021a; Sun et al. 2024; Ahmed et al. 2024a).",
